'''Abdominal obesity''', also called '''central body obesity''', is a condition involving excess fat surrounding the abdomen and an increase in waist size in humans. [[Obesity]] in this area is linked to [[diabetes mellitus type 2|Type 2 Diabetes]], insulin resistance and [[heart disease]] in humans of both genders.


